{{Thumb|{{YouTube|MWH1RA3bEz0|title=
Introducing the Avatar Marketplace | VRChat Developer Update
|thumb=File:YTThumb_MWH1RA3bEz0_AVM.webp}}}}
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
'''Avatar Marketplace''' (AVM) is a feature of VRChat’s [[Special:MyLanguage/Creator Economy|Creator Economy]], providing a platform for creators to sell monetized [[Special:MyLanguage/avatars|avatars]] directly within VRChat using [[Special:MyLanguage/Creator Economy#VRChat_Credits|VRC Credits]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Overview ==
The Avatar Marketplace allows for users to buy and use avatars from creators natively within VRChat, streamlining the process compared to third-party platforms. Purchased avatars can be immediately used without uploading them via Unity or the [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat SDK|VRChat SDK]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Selecting the '''Avatars''' Quick Link in the [[Special:MyLanguage/Quick Menu|Quick Menu]] opens the Avatar tab in the [[Special:MyLanguage/Main Menu|Main Menu]], defaulting to the '''Explore''' section. This section features both free [[Special:MyLanguage/Public Avatars|public avatars]] and paid avatars available via the Marketplace.
</div>
