<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Product listings ==
</div>
[[File:AVM-ProductListingExample.webp|thumb|<span lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">An example of a marketplace listing.</span>]]
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Each avatar listing includes images, a preview of the base model and [[Special:MyLanguage/Impostors|impostor]] (if available), a description, price, file size, upload date, performance ranking, and relevant tags. Listings also show avatar features such as platform compatibility, visemes, eye look support, Impostors, and performance breakdowns. Avatars can also be previewed locally before purchase, only the user will see the avatar during this preview.
== Purchasing avatars ==
Purchasing an avatar with the Avatar Marketplace requires sufficient VRChat Credits on your [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat account|account's]] wallet before an avatar is bought. Users on Steam, and Meta systems are currently able to purchase credits<ref>[https://help.vrchat.com/hc/en-us/articles/23255458227987-Creator-Economy-Frequently-Asked-Questions 'Creator Economy: Frequently Asked Questions'] on ''help.vrchat.com''; retrieved May 25, 2025.</ref> at a minimum quantity of 600, up to a maximum of {{formatnum:12,000}} per purchase.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
When a user has sufficient credits, they can purchase an avatar, which becomes bound to their VRChat account. Users are not yet able to purchase avatars for other users, or have the ability to download or modify their purchased avatar(s) using the VRChat SDK.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Selling on the Avatar Marketplace ==
</div>
[[File:Vrcshop_anime.webp|thumb|<span lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">Various avatars can be browsed in the [[Special:MyLanguage/Shop|Shop]]</span>]]
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
<small>''See also: [[Special:MyLanguage/Creator_Economy#Enrolling_in_the_Creator_Economy_Program|Enrolling in the Creator Economy]] for more detailed information.''</small>
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Creators interested in selling avatars on the Avatar Marketplace, are required to review the Creator Economy Program terms and conditions<ref>[https://hello.vrchat.com/legal/economy 'Creator Economy Program Rules'] on ''hello.vrchat.com''; retrieved May 25, 2025.</ref>, and must [https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/vrc-econ-apply submit an enrollment application] to be reviewed by VRChat, and approved.
</div>
[[File:Vrcshop_animefilters.webp||thumb|200x200px|<span lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">Similarly, various tags can be found through filtering within the Shop.</span>]]
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
It should be noted that the Creator Economy program for worlds and groups is separate from the Avatar Marketplace program and must be applied for separately, even if the creator is already in Creator Economy for worlds and groups.
